(212, 'z', 'SPPK003', 'Cooking Aids and Essence', NULL, 'products/SPPK003-L.jpg', 'jpg', NULL, NULL, 'Krinos', 'Mastic Gum - Chios Mastika', NULL, 'Mastic is produced exclusively in Greece, on the island of Chios, which is believed to have been Homer\'s birthplace. Mastic is a white resin that comes from the Mastic tree. Mastic is shaped like a crystal teardrop. Upon chewing it, Mastic\'s coniferrous flavor disappears and you’re left with a pliable bit of chewing gum. Mastic resin is distributed worldwide for confectionary, industrial, and pharmaceutical purposes. Products that are made from Mastic gum include; medical creams, toothpaste, cosmetics, and paint varnish. Mastic is also a prominent ingredient used for Greek breads, spices, Turkish delight, liquers, and candy. Recent medical research has demonstrated that Chios mastic actually heals abdominal ulcers.', '24-', '0.6 oz. (17g)', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'YES', '7.99', '0.40', 'NO', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 16, NULL, 21),
