(217, 'z', 'GRFY005', 'Couscous and Flours', 'Pre-Packed', 'products/GRFY005-L.jpg', 'jpg', NULL, NULL, 'Yara', 'Moroccan Couscous Medium', NULL, 'Couscous the most famous part of North African cuisine, used as the main ingredient in many dishes. Couscous is often referred to as Moroccan, but this is incorrect. It is equally a dish of Algeria, Tunisia and Libya, people of all countries may claim to be the home of couscous. Over the last decade, it\'s cropped up on American menus and dinner tables.', '12-', '24 oz. (680g)', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'YES', '2.99', '2.00', 'NO', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 17, 5, 9),
(218, 'z', 'GRFY007', 'Couscous and Flours', 'Pre-Packed', 'products/GRFY007-L.jpg', 'jpg', NULL, NULL, 'Yara', 'Whole Wheat Couscous', NULL, 'Regular couscous is made from semolina wheat, while whole-wheat couscous derives from the whole grains of durum flour. This flour derives from durum wheat, which is high in protein and commonly used for other fare like pasta and pizza dough. A whole grain has its endosperm, germ and bran intact. These components make up the kernels of grains, which contain all the nutrients. When grains are refined, at least a portion of the endosperm, germ or bran is removed. This is what makes whole wheat couscous a good addition to a healthy diet plan.', '12-', '24 oz. (680g)', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'YES', '3.49', '2.00', 'NO', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 17, 5, 9),
(219, 'z', 'GRFY017', 'Couscous and Flours', 'Pre-Packed', 'products/GRFY017-L.jpg', 'jpg', NULL, NULL, 'Yara', 'Lebanese Couscous - Moghrabieh', NULL, 'Moghrabieh or what is known as Lebanese couscous for many, is the name of small white dough balls. It is used with meat or chicken and chickpeas with specific spices. Moghrabieh’s best feature is its capacity to inflate and hold aromas; the more it is soaked in something the more it will engorge in its flavor. So what you see as little balls in the beginning can turn into soft, chewy pearls with the taste of all the ingredients accompanying them.', '12-', '28 oz. (794g)', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'YES', '4.49', '2.00', 'NO', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 17, 5, 9),
(220, 'z', 'GRFY019', 'Couscous and Flours', 'Pre-Packed', 'products/GRFY019-L.jpg', 'jpg', NULL, NULL, 'Yara', 'Palestinian Couscous - Maftool', NULL, 'You may have come across the terms couscous, Moghrabiah or Maftoul. They may seem like tongue twisters at first but they are actually three variants of  hand-rolled pasta that are versatile and tasty. What sets maftoul apart from couscous or moghrabieh is the size of the pasta granules. Couscous has the smallest granules (about 1 mm in diameter)  while moghrabiah has the largest (about the size of chickpeas). Maftoul is middle ground between the two. Maftoul’s hand rolled tiny pasta pearls are 2-3 mm in diameter  and they are made out of a mixture of whole wheat and all purpose flour rolled around a center of bulgur which gives it a nutty earthy note that is unique and a slightly deeper color.Couscous on the other hand is made out of pure white flour and it is rolled around a center of semolina giving it a lighter color and a more neutral taste. Maftoul use as a bed for stew, meat or vegetables, or try it as an entrée with your favorite pasta sauce and salads.', '12-', '20 oz. (566g)', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'YES', '4.49', '1.70', 'NO', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 17, 5, 9),
(221, 'z', 'GRFD000', 'Couscous and Flours', 'Pre-Packed', 'products/GRFD000-L.jpg', 'jpg', NULL, NULL, 'Dari', 'Couscous Barley - Al Belboula', NULL, 'Dari Belboula is the first industrial couscous in the world that is made of barley. Prepared under strict standards of quality and hygiene, it is the fruit of a long process of elaboration which has allowed it to become an essential part of the Moroccan culinary art.', '12-', '2.2 lbs. (1 kg)', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'YES', '2.99', '2.50', 'NO', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 17, 5, 48),
