(304, 'z', 'CHKA001', 'Dairy', 'Kasseri and Kashkaval', 'products/CHKA001-L.jpg', 'jpg', NULL, 'R', 'Krinos', 'Kefalograviera Greek Cheese', NULL, 'Kefalograviera is one of the newer Greek cheeses. Production was started in the 1960s and it has quickly become a favorite table cheese. This pale golden-yellow cheese has a full bodied yet pleasant and light aroma that falls between Kasseri and Kefalotiri in hardness, but with a more sharp and salty taste. Kefalograviera makes a tasty impression when grated into pasta, souffles’, pies, as well as meat and poultry dishes. It is great when paired with bread and home-made jam, and is exceptionally delicious when fried to make Saganaki cheese. Produced in Greece.', '12-', 'Approx 2 lbs.', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'NO', NULL, NULL, 'NO', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 20, 5, 21),
