(314, 'z', 'DAR011', 'Dairy', 'Jameed and Kishk', 'products/DAR011-L.jpg', 'jpg', NULL, NULL, 'Jameedna', 'Liquid Jameed - Soup Starter', NULL, 'Jameed is a defatted and dehydrated yogurt most commonly used in the popular Jordanian dish called \"Mansaff\". Cooking Instructions: Clean the lamb or the chicken meat before cooking. Put the lamb or chicken meat in a cooking pot, add water to cover the meat or chicken, you may add black pepper, cinnamon, bay leaves, saffron and cardamom to the water to enhance taste. Start boiling the contents while separating the foam until the meat is cooked. Strain the meat, keeping the cooked meat in the cooking pot while pouring the hot meat broth into a separate pot. Shake the Jameedna very well. Use scissors to cut the bag from its upper corner. Pour the required quantity of the Jameedna into a clean pot. Mix one cup of Jameedna with one and half cups of meat broth. Add the obtained Jameed Meat Broth to the meat. Start heating the meat with the Jameedna and keep cooking for at least fifteen minutes. Product of Jordan.', '8-', '2.2 lbs. (1000g)', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'YES', '9.99', '2.80', 'NO', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 20, 5, 71),
