(482, 'z', 'NUTPL001', 'Nuts and Seeds - Raw', 'Nuts and Seeds - Bulk', 'products/NUTPL001-L.jpg', 'jpg', NULL, NULL, 'Chef Ramzi', 'Pistachios', NULL, 'Naturally raw with no shell pistachios. The health benefits of pistachios have been documented: Pistachios are a naturally cholesterol-free snack that contains just 1.5g of saturated fat. You can obtain more dietary fiber from a serving of pistachios that ½ cup of broccoli or spinach, and the same amount of dietary fiber as an orange or apple. Pistachios are a great source of protein and can serve as an alternative to meat, poultry or beans, according to the USDA Food Guide Pyramid. Pistachios, like olive oil, primarily contain monounsaturated fat that has been linked with lowering cholesterol levels and the risk of heart disease. One serving of pistachios has as much potassium as half a large banana. Pistachios contain more than 10% of the Daily Value of dietary fiber and essential vitamins and minerals like B-6, thiamin, copper and phosphorus.  Pistachios are especially rich in phytosterols, which are directly associated with lowering cholesterol. According to the US FDA, “Scientific evidence suggests but does not prove that eating 1.5 ounces per day of most nuts, such as pistachios, as part of a diet low in saturated fat and cholesterol, may reduce the risk of heart disease.” They can be eaten whole, chopped, or ground, or can be added to cookies, cakes, and other desserts, or used in salads.', NULL, '10 lbs.', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'NO', NULL, NULL, 'NO', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 12, 5, 33),
