(609, 'z', 'SPA001', 'Spices and Herbs', 'Pre-Packed', 'products/SPA001-L.jpg', 'jpg', NULL, NULL, 'Adonis', 'Aleppo Pepper', NULL, 'The Aleppo is a rare chili from the region of Northern Syria and Southern Turkey. Also called the Halaby pepper. There are a few peppers named Aleppo one is a Cayenne type. This is the more rare Pimento type. The Aleppo pepper is named after the famous city of Aleppo that is on the famous silk road that was used to trade spices and goods as early as 200 B.C. it ran from North Africa though Arabia, Persia, Turkey and China. Aleppo peppers have a sweet taste with a nice kick of heat.', '12-', '100g.', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'YES', '2.99', '0.50', 'NO', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 58, 59, 32),
(610, 'z', 'SPA003', 'Spices and Herbs', 'Pre-Packed', 'products/SPA003-L.jpg', 'jpg', NULL, NULL, 'Adonis', 'Allspice Ground', NULL, 'Allspice has a complex aroma, hence its name. It is an aromatic spice with a taste similar to a combination of cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg, but hotter and more peppery. Allspice is one of the most important ingredients of Caribbean cuisine. It is used in Caribbean jerk seasoning (the wood is used to smoke jerk in Jamaica, although the spice is a good substitute), in mole sauces, and in pickling; it is also an ingredient in commercial sausage preparations and curry powders. Allspice is also indispensable in Middle Eastern cuisine, particularly in the Levant where it is used to flavor a variety of stews and meat dishes. In Palestinian cuisine, for example, many main dishes call for allspice as the sole spice added for flavoring. Allspice is commonly used in Great Britain and appears in many dishes, including in cakes. Even in many countries where allspice is not very popular in the household, such as Germany, it is used in large amounts by commercial sausage makers. Allspice is also a main flavor used in barbecue sauces.', '12-', '100g.', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'YES', '1.99', '0.50', 'NO', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 58, NULL, 32),
(611, 'z', 'SPA005', 'Spices and Herbs', 'Pre-Packed', 'products/SPA005-L.jpg', 'jpg', NULL, NULL, 'Adonis', 'Anise Ground', NULL, 'Anise is botanically related to dill, cumin, fennel, and caraway. This spice distinctly tastes like licorice and is commonly used in sweet and savory dishes, such as cakes, cookies, curries, fish, and shellfish.', '12-', '100g.', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'YES', '1.99', '0.50', 'NO', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 58, NULL, 32),
(612, 'z', 'SPA007', 'Spices and Herbs', 'Pre-Packed', 'products/SPA007-L.jpg', 'jpg', NULL, NULL, 'Adonis', 'Black Pepper Ground', NULL, 'Black Pepper adds flavor to almost every food of every nation in the world. Black pepper comes from the pepper plant, a smooth woody vine that can grow up to 33 feet in hot and humid tropical climates. Black pepper is an excellent source of manganese, a very good source of iron and vitamin K, and a good source of dietary fiber.', '12-', '110g.', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'YES', '4.49', '0.50', 'NO', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 58, NULL, 32);
